Britain's former tallest man was buried today in a bespoke coffin measuring almost 8ft long and remembered by friends as a 'gentle giant'.

Actor Christopher Greener, from Bromley, south London, who grew to be 7ft 6in and a half inches and weighed up to 30 stone, died last month aged 71.

More than 60 people attended his funeral today including members of the Tall Cub of Great Britain and eight pallbearers were needed to carry him.

His best friend Berry Tolson, who met Mr Greener 50 years ago when they both played for the London Latvian Basketball Klub, said he was so tall he could put the ball into the net with no effort.

